html
  head
    title="FreeCodeCamp Timestamp API"
    link(href='/dist/style.css', rel='stylesheet')

  body
    .wrapper
      .header
        .header__title #{title}

      .main
        .main__section
          .main__subtitle User stories:
          .main__text 1) I can pass a string as a parameter, and it will check to see whether that string contains either a unix timestamp or a natural language date (example: January 1, 2016)
          .main__text 2) If it does, it returns both the Unix timestamp and the natural language form of that date.
          .main__text 3) If it does not contain a date or Unix timestamp, it returns null for those properties.

        .main__section
          .main__subtitle Example usage:
          .main__text
            a.main__link(href="https://timestamp-4000.herokuapp.com/December 15, 2015").main__link https://timestamp-4000.herokuapp.com/December 15, 2015

          .main__text
            a.main__link(href="https://timestamp-4000.herokuapp.com/1450137600").main__link https://timestamp-4000.herokuapp.com/1450137600

        .main__section
          .main__subtitle Example output:
          .main__text.main__text--code.
            {
              "unix": 1450137600,
              "natural": "December 15, 2015"
            }

      .footer Made with hearts by
        a.footer__link(href="https://github.com/danielmoi") Daniel Moi
